<font color="#FF0000">CARL SAGAN WAS A COMMUNIST</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 18 21:20:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
Carl Sagan was a communist, The dehumaninzing question Sagan posed therefore had no value.<br>
I have a problem with an individual who accepted fiction over reality. Sagan's concept that a creator God is an outdated &quot;geocentrist conceit&quot; concocted by our less enlightened forefathers and foisted upon the human culture, as reflected in his &quot;great demotions&quot; would lead the reader to the conclusion that there is no meaning or purpose in our existence. <br>
Sagan belief therefore places no value to his question, &quot;Is it necessary to dehumanize an adversary for war?&quot;<br><br>
Sagan believed that if the Garden of Eden account was true, knowledge was denied us by God, hence we were suppose to be kept in the garden without the knowledge of good and evil. Sagan believed that because we were starved for knowledge we broke out of the garden and are better off. He failed to realize that once we left the garden we had the opportunity to seek out GOOD as well as evil.<br><br>
It is in this, not the dehumanizing of individuals that we should be concern about. It was the problem we encountered in the field of Vietnam. The age old struggle between between Good and Evil. Having seen the destruction, murder and killing of south Vietnamese villiagers by the nVA (communist soldiers) made it a lot simplier to kill them in the fields of battle. <br>
  <br>
For all his greatness, poor Carl could not see the invisible things formed by a creator that can be clearly seen. He spent all that time gazing at the stars but could not see them. He could not comprehend that they can be understood by the things that are made, by what is visible all around us even a creators eternal power and this poor Sagan could not understand this simple truth and died without excuse.&quot; <br>
Carl Sagan rejected the evidences he could clearly see. The masterful design clearly visible in the universe. Although he expressed a reluctant need to find a Designer, he gave up on that search and constructed his own &quot;Tower of Babel.&quot; Sought to make men in the image of sinful men, Carl Sagan is not one I would see as an individual to be admired, studied or listened to. <br><br>
But, look at the beautiful fields, the rice farm land and the beauty of the jungles of Vietnam and there is where we honor the creator of men, and men made in the image of God. But those that rejected the creators involvement in our world  (communism) to them those fields have no value, no beauty. They were seen only as food and men as the means of gathering wealth and honor. Those people of the South to the northern gook were less then human and they were to be conquered. To them the South Vietnamese had no value. I believe GOOK is a very passive word compared to what God call those that embrace the communistic denial of a divine being.<br><br>
The question should be, What does it matter what you call an individual you are going to kill. <br><br>
 <br><br>

